<TITLE> Govt allocates funds for product development </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 06 (bdnews24.com)  The government has allocated Tk 146 crore to open ceramics, leather, textiles and mineral resources departments at five engineering universities. The Project to Open New Academic Departments in Five Public Universities and Develop Structural and Laboratory Facilities was approved by the Executive Committee of the National Economic Council on Tuesday. Habib Ullah Majumder, secretary of the planning division, told the reporters after the ECNEC meeting, two ceramics departments will be opened at the Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology (BUET) and Rajshahi University of Engineering and Technology (RUET). H e said a mineral resources and petroleum department is planned for Chittagong University of Engineering and Technology (CUET); a department on leather engineering is to be opened at Khulna University of Engineering and Technology (KUET) and a department on textiles engineering is to be opened at Dhaka University of Engineering and Technology (DUET). The ECNEC meeting with prime minister Sheikh Hasina in the chair also approved three other projects totalling Tk 133 crore. They are Renovation and Development of Chittagong Jahar Ahsad Choudhury Stadium as a Venue for World Cup 2011 at a cost of Tk 52 crore; Renovation and Development of Khulna Sheikh Abu Naser Stadium as a Venue for World Cup 2011 at a cost of Tk 52 crore and Construction of National Archives Building: Second Phase (Ammended) at a cost of Tk 29 crore. b
